Functional Requirements

The system shall include an interactive map where users can post their Offers and Needs.

Each Offer or Need shall contain a short description (e.g., “Reading stories with children”, “Help with homework”).

Users shall describe their Offers and Needs using semantic tags (e.g., cooking, tutoring, companionship, errands, storytelling).

One hour of any service shall equal one TimeBank hour.

Every user shall be able to both give and receive services.

Non-Functional Requirements 

The architecture shall be designed to support a culture of mutual support and cooperation.

The interface shall be simple and welcoming, reflecting inclusiveness and mutual support rather than competition.
